1. Consists of federal government investment grants for highways, transit, air and water transportation,
and water treatment plants.
2. Consists of the implied subsidy cost of government acquisition of assets such as shares of preferred
stock or warrants from private business.
3. Consists of maritime construction subsidies and, beginning with 2009, the homebuyer tax credit
provision of the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act of 2009.
4. Beginning with October 2002, consists of payments to the Uniformed Services Retiree Health Care Fund
to amortize the unfunded liability.
5. Consists of forgiveness of debts owed by foreign governments to the U.S. government, and
the December 1999 transfer to the Republic of Panama of the U.S. government's assets in the
Panama Canal Commission. Includes capital grants paid to the U.S. territories and the
Commonwealths of Puerto Rico and Northern Mariana Islands, and the implied subsidy cost of
government acquisition of preferred stock and warrants from banks in Puerto Rico through the
Troubled Assset Relief Program.
